ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's a math class. If you don't like math or flipped classrooms, stay away. If you need it for your major or to get to the next level of math, you just have to power through it.
Take it if you're interested in math or need it for your major.
Yes I would. I enjoyed the class
Math 115 is a flipped classroom where you learn the basic material through video's. The material and more difficult applications are then reinforced in class and in problem sets.
I would recommend it but say that self study is an important supplement to the flipped classroom

Math 115 is very difficult but interesting. Flipped classroom can be difficult but it is nice to have the videos to go back and watch again. Exams are long and very difficult. Felt like they were meant to trip us up. Problem sets were fair. If you like math or reccomend but it takes a lot of time.
It is an interesting and helpful course, but I do not recommend taking it when flipped.

It's just like any other calc 2 course. I would recommend it if the student likes math. I think the class experience depends very much on the instructor. I happened to have a wonderful instructor. I have friends who had terrible ones.

It's kinda hard, and the second midterm is worse than the first just because the material is harder. Just stay on top of the material as you see it and you'll be fine. Plus there's so many great teachers and review sessions that it's hard to not do well.
I would recommend this course to a fellow student.
I would say the it is not as easy as you would expect it to be. I took BC Calc in high school, and I still ended up learning a lot in this class.
I would only recommend this course if they had already covered part of the content as it was assumed the first few classes had been covered in high school.
A brief, condensed version of AP Calc BC with a HUGE emphasis on sequences and series. Take it! A manageable course, as long as you get a good TA.
Math 115 is a standard Calc II class. I would recommend it to anyone who needs to take it or who likes math. It's a challenge, but it's not too bad.
Boycott the entire math department until flipped classes are eradicated.
